    <key>CBReleaseWhatsNew</key>
    <string>Polling now backs off automatically when claude.ai rate-limits an account; row badge shows the wait.
Opening the menu refreshes immediately and polls faster for 5 minutes (toggle in Settings).
Background keep-alive pings idle web sessions every few hours so cookies don't lapse.
Polling and auto-swap now start at app launch — no need to open the menu first.
Diagnostics → Web usage shows the keep-alive heartbeat at a glance.</string>
    <key>CBReleaseHotfixes</key>
    <string>Fixed auto-swap and token refresh not running after a Sparkle update until the menu was opened.</string>
    <key>CBReleaseKnownIssues</key>
    <string>The keep-alive heartbeat first appears ~3–5 hours after launch — earlier than that the Diagnostics row reads "no ping yet" by design.</string>
